  "prompt": "What are some great examples of witty exchanges ?",
  "response": "Sure! Here are some classic examples of witty exchanges:\n\n1. **Winston Churchill vs. Lady Astor**:\n    Lady Astor: \"If I were your wife, I\u2019d put poison in your coffee.\"\n    Churchill: \"If I were your husband, I\u2019d drink it.\"\n\n2. **Dorothy Parker**:\n    When asked to use the word \"horticulture\" in a sentence:\n    \"You can lead a horticulture, but you can't make her think.\"\n\n3. **Groucho Marx**:\n    Woman: \"I want to have my baby here.\"\n    Groucho: \"I don\u2019t blame you, madam, this is as good a place as any.\"\n\n4. **Mark Twain**:\n    \"I have never killed a man, but I have read many obituaries with great pleasure.\"\n\n5. **Oscar Wilde**:\n    \u201cI can resist everything except temptation.\u201d\n\n6. **Dr. Leonard McCoy (Star Trek)**:\n    Captain Kirk: \"What am I, Doctor?\"\n    McCoy: \"You're an overgrown boy scout.\"\n\n7. **Noel Coward**:\n    Woman: \"I'm the only woman who can take her clothes off and leave them on.\"\n    Coward: \"Now, that\u2019s not fair.\"\n\nThese examples are known for their quick wit and clever repartee, showcasing the humor and intelligence of the speakers.",
